Noor trailer: Meet the goofy, joker journalist, Sonakshi Sinha 
7-3-2017 
Bollywood actor Sonakshi Sinha revealed the first trailer of her much-awaited film, Noor on Tuesday afternoon. The film is the Bollywood adaptation of the 2014 Pakistani novel by journalist-writer Saba Imtiaz, Karachi, You’re Killing Me!

Sonakshi in a still from Noor.

The two-and-a-half-minute-long trailer introduces our star - Sonakshi, the “joker journalist” - who wants to celebrate her birthday or cover train accidents but is forced to go for a Sunny Leone interview. After a series of her goof-ups, the tragedy or the turning point of the story pops up.

Purab Kohli plays Sonakshi’s love interest in the film.

Read more

Noor is directed by Sunhil Sippy and stars Sonakshi Sinha in the lead role alongside, Kanan Gill, Shibani Dandekar, Purab Kohli.

The film releases on 21 April 2017.

